✅ STEP 1: Create Your Project Folder

Make a folder, for example:

ts-task-manager/


Inside it, create one file:

tasks.ts


Paste your TypeScript code inside tasks.ts.

✅ STEP 2: Install TypeScript (if not installed)

Open Terminal / CMD and run:

npm install -g typescript


Check version:

tsc -v

✅ STEP 3: Compile tasks.ts → tasks.js

Open terminal inside your folder:

cd path/to/ts-task-manager


Then run:

tsc tasks.ts


After compiling, a new file is created:

tasks.js

✅ STEP 4: Run JavaScript file with Node.js

Run:

node tasks.js

  
